body:
Accommodating growth
The City Centre Zone plays a significant role in accommodating residential, business and supporting community service growth, and has sufficient serviced development capacity and additional infrastructure to meet its short, medium and long term residential and business growth needs, including:
A variety of building type, size, affordability and distribution, including forms of high-density housing;
Convenient access to active and public transport activity options;
Efficient, well integrated and strategic use of available development sites; and
Convenient access to a range of open space, including green space, and supporting commercial activity and community facility options.

