body:
City development outcomes
Recognise the positive outcomes that developments either over the height thresholds or under minimum building heights in the City Centre Zone can make to a well-functioning urban environment, as compensation for adverse effects, through the provision of enduring outcomes that provide public benefit and positively contribute to the sense of place and distinctive form, quality and amenity of the City Centre, including:
Positively contributing to public space provision and the amenity of the site and surrounding area, particularly in areas of deficit public space;
Positively contributing to public accessibility and connections;
Restoring and reusing heritage buildings and structures;
Recognising or responding to adjacent sites and area of heritage or sites and areas of significance to Māori; and
Incorporating assisted housing into the development; where this is provided, legal instruments are required to ensure that it remains assisted housing for at least 25 years.

