body:
Sense of place
Provide for good quality new development and supporting public space that reinforces the City Centre’s identity and unique sense of place at a city scale, including its:
Surrounding topography and harbour setting;
Rich Māori and tauiwi/non-Māori history;
Compact, walkable city structure;
Diversified and vibrant mix of activities;
Visually prominent buildings and variety of architectural styles; and
Diversity of accessible, well designed civic and public space.

